        <section id="memory" class="fourth-section">
            <h1>Memory Management</h1>
            <div class="main-area">
                <div class="main-area-left"></div>
                <div class="main-area-center">
                    <p>Memory management controls how RAM is used so programs can run smoothly.</p>
                    <img src="img/memory.png" alt="OS Memory Management">
                    <h2>What it does:</h2>
                    <ul class="no-margin">
                        <li>Gives memory to programs when they start</li>
                        <li>Takes memory back when they close</li>
                        <li>Uses virtual memory to extend RAM using storage</li>
                        <li>Protects memory so apps don't overwrite each other</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Example: </strong>
                        If too many apps are open, the OS may slow down because RAM is full.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="main-area-right">
