        <section id="file" class="fifth-section">
            <h1>File System</h1>
            <div class="main-area">
                <div class="main-area-left"></div>
                <div class="main-area-center">
                    <p>The file system organizes and stores data on disks (SSD/HDD).</p>
                    <img src="img/file.png" alt="OS Memory Management">
                    <h2>What it does:</h2>
                    <ul class="no-margin">
                        <li>Creates, deletes, and organizes files/folders</li>
                        <li>Keeps track of where files are stored</li>
                        <li>Controls permissions (who can access files)</li>
                        <li>Helps prevent data corruption</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Examples of file systems: </strong>NTFS (Windows), APFS (macOS), and ext4 (Linux)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="main-area-right">
