        <section class="eight-section" id="security">
            <h1>Security & User Management</h1>
            <div class="main-area">
                <div class="main-area-left"></div>
                <div class="main-area-center">
                    <p>Operating systems protect the system and manage multiple users.</p>
                    <img src="img/security.png" alt="OS User Interface">
                    <h2>Security features include:</h2>
                    <ul class="no-margin">
                        <li>User accounts and passwords</li>
                        <li>Permissions and access control</li>
                        <li>Encryption (protecting stored data)</li>
                        <li>Updates and patches to fix vulnerabilities</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Example: </strong>A standard user account can't install system-wide software without admin permission.</p>
